713367f-b.text:
616-626 West 48th Street, south aide, between Eleventh and Twelfth
Aves. No. 626 is a 2-story frame house.
April 21, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
A View at the Hudson River extremity of 48th Street. Note the new French Line Terminal (Pier No. 88) and the also new "Normandie" alongside. Frame structure (No. 626) is distinctly apparent on
the left.
June 5, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
